  "text": "Fluorescence ratios of scanned images of arrays were obtained using Bluefuse version 3.2 (BlueGnome, Cambridge, UK). After mapping to Human Mar. 2006 assembly (hg18), 27,801 unique positions were identified. The log 2 ratios were then normalised to their mode values by using the R/Bioconductor package limma [CITATION_1] . For ease of annotation, data points differing from the normal reference sample with a log 2 ratio of greater than 0.5 or less than -0.5 were considered gains or losses, respectively.",
